A total of Sh50 million has been disbursed through the Affirmative Action Fund in Trans Nzoia since its inception in 2014.Woman representative Janet Nangabo (pictured) on Wednesday said the funds have helped improve lives.She spoke after distributing cheques to help 80 groups to buy tents and water tanks, pay school fees and engage in other profit-making activities.Nangabo urged the beneficiaries to invest in projects that will help alleviate poverty.Sh6 million will cater for school fees for people living with disabilities and orphans. Nangabo urged the national government to increase funding to help reach more residents.Last year, Gender CS Sicily Kariuki said the government is satisfied with how affirmative action funds are being used by groups.